          "INC-SPECT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The uranium fission neutron spectrum is disturbed even",
                "before reaching the light water moderator by the fuel",
                "rod itself in which uranium (8% wt., 20% enriched) is",
                "dispersed homogeneously in zirconium hydride (91% wt.",
                "Zr, and 1% wt. H). However, taking into account the",
                "agreement of the two values, i.e., the measured",
                "fission neutron flux using the well accepted cross",
                "section of 105 mb for the Ni-58(n,p)Co-58 monitor",
                "reaction and the flux calculated by General Atomic, it",
                "can probably be concluded that the spectrum at the",
                "midpoint of the central thimble is not disturbed",
                "significantly from the unmoderated fission neutron",
                "spectrum for the average cross section measurement."
              ]
            }
          ],
